						<summary>

						<p>Records the gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold as tested and weighed by <hi rend="italic">dhanmakkaṭṭaḷai</hi> by Poṟkōyil Mūvāyiravan (alias ?) Chaturaṉ, the Trai-rājya-ghaṭika <hi rend="italic">madhyastha</hi> of Rājamallach-chaturvēdimaṅgalam of Tiruvēkambapuram in Dāmaṟk-Kōṭṭam for maintaining a brāhmaṉa, who was to workship the deity during the three <hi rend="italic">sandhis</hi> and to perform mid-night service. </p>						

						</summary>
